 or discussion the vast majority of file types are supported including image pdf microsoft word excel and powerpoint files reminders     reminders are automatic emails that are set to remind you or your team members of upcoming task deadlines event dates or task commencement notification rules sheet sheet sheet sheet notifications are automatic emails that are sent when changes are made to a sheet notification rules give you the ability to specify the conditions under which an email is triggered to alert recipients comments     comments give you the ability to have and save conversations with others about the work that you’re doing activity log       activity log is a single place to view and filter on all of the activities and changes made to a sheet you can see who viewed your sheet whom it was shared with what changes were made and when filter by user date range and action types to find exactly what you’re looking for views card view     display tasks on cards categorize cards into lanes to organize your work more visually drag and drop cards into different lanes to move work through a process gantt chartscritical path     show task and crossproject dependencies hierarchy milestones percentage complete custom fields critical path and filters calendar view     the calendar view will display all the dates contained in a sheet or report in a calendar format you can also sync your sheet to your google calendar user administration user mgmt groups      assign system administrators who can add and remove users and manage sheet ownership assign group admins who can create groups for sharingsending to multiple users resource management      view allocation of key people across projects single sign on sso        enable the use of corporate logon credentials using saml based single signon sso service saml supports adfs  okta onelogin ping identity vmware horizon shibboleth enterprise access control        enterprise controls allow you to control what domains users can share to control sheet publication features define what types of files users can attach define custom welcome screens for your users and automatically add licensed users within designated email domains to your plan solution building sights   view only view only sights can help you visualize summarize and share important aspects of your work such as project status or whether youre on target with key performance indicators kpis a sight can also help you stay organized by providing a hub or central location for related resources such as collections of sheets or reports forms     configure and publish web based forms for collecting data into a sheet common uses include collecting survey data customer feedback and applicant information custom color and logos      customize the color and logo of your smartsheet account web forms and workspaces integrations g suite     smartsheet enables gmail and g suite users to request updates via gmail import contacts from gmail merge data with docs collaborate over hangouts attach and retrieve files from drive import and export to sheets sync with calendar and utilize enterprise sso via oauth o      smartsheet enables office  users to create or edit smartsheet tasks from within both outlook and outlook mobile attach files from onedrive importexport to excel and project collaborate with skype for business requires smartsheet enterprise or business plan gain insights from power bi automate workflows with flow and sign on to smartsheet with azure active directory     if you have uploaded files to your google drive onedrive dropbox box evernote or egnyte account you can attach a direct link to those files to a smartsheet workspace sheet row or discussion api calls     the smartsheet api enables customers to programmatically access and manage their organizations smartsheet account and data it is designed to be simple and intuitive and is based on widely accepted standards and conventions including rest json and http success and error codes if you already have experience with other publicly available restful apis you will feel right at home live data connector       connect live smartsheet data to analytics tools like tableau excel qlik and spotfire using an industrystandard odbc connector salesforce optional contact us contact us   smartsheet for salesforce enables powerful collaboration capabilities for sales teams to organize update and share customer information with internal and external team members data is automatically synchronized whether edited in smartsheet or salesforce ensuring all stakeholders are viewing the most uptodate information jira optional contact us contact us   smartsheet for jira provides visibility into it and software development projects being tracked in jira issues are automatically synchronized whether edited in smartsheet or jira ensuring every record is up to date see fewer features frequently asked questions changes with smartsheet you are never locked into a plan that does not fit you can add or remove users change plans or cancel your subscription at anytime payment we accept visa mastercard discover american express credit cards paypal and for annual team business and enterprise plans we can invoice you invoices can be paid by credit card check wire or ach currencies we can accept payments in usd  us dollar aud  australian dollar cad  canadian dollar eur € euro gbp £ british pound jpy ¥ japanese yen nonprofits smartsheet strongly supports non profit causes with discounts on annual plans individual yr yr yr €yr £yr ¥yr per user team yr yr yr €yr £yr ¥yr per user  user minimum business yr yr yr €yr £yr ¥yr per user  user minimum just tell us about your organization during the check out process try smartsheet for free have questions let us help live chat about us  smartsheet skip to main content productproduct tour apps  integrations solutionsby functionproject management it  operations sales marketing software deve